{"questionId":"22040","questionHtml":"<p>Determine, with justification, whether the equilibrium point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> is stable or unstable.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>two (distinct) real negative eigenvalues&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p>(or equivalent (<em>eg</em> both&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math>))</p>\n<p>⇒&nbsp;stable equilibrium point&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22040","referenceCode":"21M.2.AHL.TZ2.7c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Determine, with justification, whether the equilibrium point (0, 0) is stable or unstable.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}